	abstract = {This review presents the modern ways to solve some vital problems that have appeared in the studies of the matter fluxes in the hydrosphere using radioactive tracers. In recent years, the variety of radionuclides applied was widened and the methods for registration of radioactive emissions were notably modified and upgraded, as well as the procedures of separation and concentration of elements. Meanwhile, up to now, these changes have not been represented in Russian scientific publications and have not been introduced into the common practice of marine expeditions and analytical laboratories. The review considers short-living radionuclides (234Th, 210Pb, 210Po, 7Be, 32P, 33P, etc.) applicable for the studies of rapid changes in the marine enviroment. Copyright © 2005 by Pleiades Publishing, Inc.},
