	abstract = {The radioactive beryllium (Be) levels in sewage sludge were analyzed. It was observed that the Be levels in the sludge were up to three orders of magnitude higher than the accepted level of radioactivity in domestic water supplies. 7Be activities upto 40 Bq/kg above the background were recorded and no appreciable activity was found in the liquid disinfected specimens. Analysis suggests the preparation of soil-additives from the sludge only after about 5 half-lives have elapsed.},
